description.narrative: The year 2019 saw the approval by the Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Policy (MHLSP) of the Child Care and Development Standards that include as a key component universal progressive Home Visiting for children aged 0-3 developed with UNICEF support. To ensure sustainability related curricula were developed, approved and implemented for the Medical University and Medical College, as well as for the National Center for Continuous Medical Education of Nurses including pre- and in-service home-visiting modules. In 2019 UNICEF continued to provide support to the MHLSP in implementation Communication Strategy on raising the demand for immunization. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2020
